What We Do | Prolocor What We Do the problem the solution patients doctors How We Do It our approach the test Who We Are prolocor our team advisors Get In Touch What We Do problem CV disease is the leading cause of death and disability around the world 1 . USA adults have coronary artery disease (CAD) 2 people with acute coronary syndromes (ACS) people suffer a new or recurrent stroke 1 Worldwide people have atherosclerotic CV disease in the 7 major markets (US + EU4 + UK + Japan) deaths each year due to atherosclerotic cardiovascular disease problem While highly effective as an antithrombotic treatment, dual antiplatelet therapy (DAPT) is associated with an increased risk of bleeding 1 . As a result, physicians struggle with a dilemma: which patients have a high enough risk of acute coronary events, such that the risk of bleeding is outweighed by the benefit of the antithrombotic therapy? We want to help simplify this learn how this problem impacts patients learn how this problem impact doctors solution Schneider in the Schneider in the We are developing a novel predictive test that is the first to measure FcyRIIa, a biomarker found on the surface of Many tests available today look at the reactivity of platelets to antithrombotic drugs like aspirin or clopidogrel, to assess A large analyzed the predictive ability of nearly such tests across more than studies 3 . The consensus? There remains a need to develop predictive biomarkers that can much more effectively guide individualized therapy for patients with cardiovascular At Prolocor, we are developing a novel test based on FcyRIIa, a protein expressed on the surface of platelets, the blood cells that are involved in thrombosis or clot formation . Most importantly, the expression of FcyRIIa is significantly increased in certain patients with atherosclerotic cardiovascular In those patients, we see a significantly increased risk of subsequent CV events, compared to patients without a corresponding increase in FcyRIIa This dichotomy has enabled us to leverage FcyRIIa as a predictive biomarker for cardiovascular patients Our hope is that the FcyRIIa test will benefit the treatment of two groups of cardiovascular “Patients at low risk should benefit from shortened treatment with more powerful antiplatelet ” Resulting in reduced bleeding Resulting in reduced recurrent thrombotic “Patients at high risk should derive greater absolute benefit from long term treatment with more powerful antiplatelet ” doctors Our hope is that the FcyRIIa test will help physicians solve the dilemma: which patients have a high enough risk of acute coronary events, such that the risk of bleeding is outweighed by the benefit of the antithrombotic therapy? references Virani SS, et Heart disease and stroke statistics—2020 update: a report from the American Heart 141:e139–e596. American Heart Cardiovascular Disease: A Costly Burden for Projections through Wisman PP, et Journal of Thrombosis and Haemostasis, : –747. Boylan B, et Blood 112:2780–6. Schneider DJ, Arterioscler Thromb Vasc Biol 29:1138–43. Home • Kojin Therapeutics Menu About Team Investors Join Us Drugging the sensitive cell state Contact Us Join Our Team Join Our Team Drugging the sensitive cell state Our Science We translate our deep biological insight into cell states to Our approach opens new avenues for the treatment of cancer, fibrosis, ischemia, and immune Traditional Approach Traditional therapeutic approaches focus on cell types defined by location and This anatomical view limits our ability to understand similarities of cells across tissues and diseases, and provides little guidance for how to target cells Cell States Cell states provide a new lens to understand differences - and similarities - in the behavior of individual Commonly shared across many distinct cell types, these internal programs dictate how a cell reacts to its While they can’t be observed directly, cell states are reflected in measurable traits of the cell, such as its pattern or how it responds to Like an individual’s personality, it is an abstract concept with Drugging cell states By drugging cell states , we can target cells The conservation of cell states across tissues and disorders enables a unified approach to treat diseases that initially appear Take our first target, the cell state . First discovered by Kojin’s founders in aggressive cancers, it is now recognized as common to cells that cause diseases such as fibrosis and immune Ferroptosis Cells in this state are vulnerable to ferroptosis , a form of cell death in which a lipid peroxidation chain reaction destroys the cell membrane like rapidly spreading We target this state to selectively cause cell death by ferroptosis, protect beneficial cells, or modulate their Kojin’s biology platform connects complex cell states to biochemical processes to deliver targets, matching patients with the right drugs to treat today’s There are trillions of tiny creatures living in your mouth, called microbes The most common of these are bacteria, viruses, and fungi and they are way too small to see with your Some of these microbes are good Helping us fight disease, digest food, and keep our teeth Some of them are bad Producing harmful byproducts like plaque and acid that can lead to cavities or cause infections like gum Bad microbes can even cause problems in the rest of your body - attacking areas like your brain and heart At Bristle, we analyze all the microbes in your mouth, collectively referred to as your oral microbiome We provide you the information you need on your oral health and risk for disease, then help you optimize with simple treatments that get rid of the bad microbes and keep the good With our approach, we help you avoid dental drills and cavity fillings so you can get back to doing the things you love Common Questions What does Bristle do? Bristle analyzes your oral microbiome to detect oral diseases, like cavities and gum disease, and at the earliest stages when they can be prevented or What is a microbe? Microbes, or microscopic organisms, are tiny living things that are found all around us and are too small to be seen by the naked The most common types are bacteria, viruses and fungi, and they live in water, soil, and in the What is a microbiome, and what does it do? A microbiome is the community of microbes living together in a particular Scientists have measured the microbiome of plants, animals, and even subway systems, to figure out which species of microbe are there, what they are doing, and how they are able to In humans, our microbiome has been found to play an important role in our Some species are healthy, while others are potentially In a healthy body the helpful and harmful species coexist without any But if there is a disturbance in that balance - from diet, antibiotic use, or other factors - the community can become unbalanced and the harmful bacteria can wreak The gut microbiome, for example, has been implicated in mental health, inflammatory bowel disease, diabetes, obesity, and What is the oral microbiome and why is it important (what can it tell you)? Similar to the gut, our mouths depend on a balanced microbiome to stay Each of us has a unique microbiome made up of, on average, bacterial species (with over that have been identified!). Mission — Centivax 0 Skip to Content Monoclonals Vaccines Oligoclonals Current Page: Mission Media Open Menu Close Menu Monoclonals Vaccines Oligoclonals Current Page: Mission Media Open Menu Close Menu Monoclonals Vaccines Oligoclonals Current Page: Mission Media Who, What, Why, and How: Centivax and its Mission [Please read a memo on Racial Injustice in our time] Centivax is a therapeutics company founded to treat, cure and eradicate the remaining complex pathogens of the century . This goal is executed by combining computational to efficiently make medicines, with a unique business strategy to make sure that we have the freedom to pursue medicines that matter and sell those medicines at a price that the world can Our computational engineering technologies were made possible by the emerging field of computational immunology, and developed by pioneers of that field over the course of 8 From our unique vantage point as the creators of these technologies, we were able to see that the true consequence of computational immunoengineering went far beyond disrupting the biologics discovery services market, and had broken open pathways to victory against many of the major outstanding druggability challenges in our generation of At heart, the technologies we had created were uniquely suited to targeting rare or challenging epitopes on polymorphic These technologies include a generalized (i.e. “universal”) vaccine technology, a influenza vaccine therapeutic candidate (i.e “universal flu shot”), multiple computationally optimized biologics libraries for generating and optimizing antibodies (i.e. “rational bnAbs”), VHHs (i.e. nanbodies), bispecifics and To ensure that we make the medicines that matter, and that those medicines can reach all the people who need them, central to Centivax’s DNA is a commitment to making all of our medicines available at close to cost in the developing world, and to run a lean business that keeps our medicines We enable this by continuing the Distributed Bio strategy of a business plan that grows reluctantly and strategically based on actual business need, minimizes reliance on venture funding to avoid incentive misalignments, partner with grant sources that share our commitment to providing subsidized medicines internationally, and always focuses on rapid product creation as a means of ensuring a sustainable R&D budget while reducing our reliance on any external funding and ensuring that our incentives are always aligned with making medicines that A note from Founding Partner, CEO & President Jacob Glanville, PhD : I grew up in Tzutujile village of Santiago Atitlan on the edge of Lake Atitlan in the Mayan highlands of There was no hospital, and resources were limited due to the ongoing civil war as well as centuries of Santiago didn’t have the fundamental civil sanitation systems or medical support that my American friends take for Growing up, I was infected with amoebas, and giardia, and worms, and other common pathogens so many times I have lost Comparatively, I was lucky: I could afford the Many of the children in the village weren’t so Many had bloated bellies, a red tinge to their hair, and stunted growth: the hallmarks of chronic pathogen burden and Missing medicines, simple medicines, could have changed many When I moved to the United States at , I was at first struck by how most people were much taller and in general took for granted their comparative good health compared to our way of life in the developing As I returned year after year to Santiago, to visit family and to carry out the four years of vaccine studies that ultimately proved the Centivax vaccine technologies, I was delighted to see how much medicine had improved after the war, and how people’s lives had improved with Tzutujile teenagers were a head taller than their parents and older People were spending the time and the resources that they used to spend on illnesses now on bettering themselves, their families, and their These observations have left me with the conviction that pathogen burden, from the microcosm of a single child to the macrocosm of all humanity, is an avoidable waste of human Some medicines just need to reach their final destination, and others need to be invented, but ultimately what happened in Santiago should happen Reducing and eliminating the global burden of disease is one of the single greatest steps that humanity can undertake to liberate our resources of Use © The Potential of Condensates Condensate Biology Role in Disease We’re writing the next chapter in cell biology Prev Next The science Faze is advancing is going to reshape the way we treat Recent discoveries in cell biology have uncovered a fundamentally new understanding of how cells In addition to the traditional organelles, scientists have discovered a growing class of “membraneless” organelles, called biomolecular condensates, which play key roles in the healthy functioning of Prev Next Biomolecular condensates are dynamic clusters which can contain proteins and nucleic acids within a They form by phase separation , a process similar to oil separating in These clusters coalesce and disperse within cells, serving as an organizational strategy to dynamically segregate certain molecules from the wider environment of the This allows cells to rapidly respond to changing conditions, such as stress and perform certain actions, such as DNA repair, signaling and intracellular Prev Next This revolutionary insight means is key for healthy cell function and has important implications in We’re advancing a dramatically new way of viewing disease Amyotrophic lateral sclerosis (ALS) Prev Next Groundbreaking research by Faze’s Paul Taylor has demonstrated that condensates are at the root of many related neurological mutations in amyotrophic lateral sclerosis (ALS), frontotemporal dementia (FTD), and inclusion body myositis (IBM) are associated with dysfunction in the assembly and behavior of a type of condensate called the stress Stress granules form in the cell Amyotrophic lateral sclerosis (ALS) Prev Next Mutations within certain proteins in a stress granule can promote greater viscosity, or “stickiness,” of the This shift alters the capacity of the condensate to disassemble and creates an environment that encourages protein aggregation within the Amyotrophic lateral sclerosis (ALS) Prev Next In the case of ALS, this can promote the formation of fibrillar aggregates of that are hallmarks of the Amyotrophic lateral sclerosis (ALS) Prev Next Faze is targeting key proteins to rebalance the dynamics of stress granules… Amyotrophic lateral sclerosis (ALS) Prev Next …thus preventing the hardening of fibrils Myotonic dystrophy (DM) Prev Next Myotonic dystrophy is linked to another condensate, referred to as aberrant nuclear RNA Myotonic dystrophy (DM) Prev Next In myotonic dystrophy, the overexpression of repeat RNAs leads to the accumulation of RNA foci in the cell These RNA foci, in turn, bind up important cellular proteins, preventing them from carrying out their normal cellular functions and leading to disease Myotonic dystrophy (DM) Prev Next Faze is working to identify the key components and regulators of these aberrant nuclear Targeting these proteins therapeutically will dissolve the nuclear foci, thus liberating sequestered proteins and restoring normal cellular © Contact Privacy About - datajoy Our story Blog Careers Get beta Home Our story Blog Careers Get beta We make it simple for companies to use data to grow revenue Our Story It began with two tech veterans A serial SaaS entrepreneur and a builder of acclaimed analytics Both encountered the same problem again and again: Why is it so hard for SaaS companies to answer basic questions about their full revenue funnel? Jon Lee Chief Executive Officer & CEO & Founder Jon started four software companies with a singular north star of helping customers make better Jon was CEO Co-founder of Copper, the leading CRM for over ,000 businesses that use Google Prior to Copper, Jon was GM at Zynga and launched Chefville, the largest game in the world by daily active players in Jon came to Zynga through its acquisition of DNA Games, the social games optimization software company he as Prior to DNA Games, Jon was CEO Co-founder of Bazaar Advertising, a search advertising technology In two years, Jon grew Bazaar organically to $47M prior to selling it to Epic Media Jon graduated from UC Berkeley with a degree in Industrial Engineering and Operations Research and lives with his family of five in Hillsborough, Ken Wong Chief Product Officer & CPO & Founder Ken has worked for + years in building acclaimed BI tools across the data stack, including 5 years at Tableau leading the latest in ML, data modeling and advanced Building the most technology gave Ken a deep appreciation of what’s possible with BI tools, but talking with customers showed him a stark reality: Most customers simply can’t leverage their advanced tools to get the basic answers they want, and more tools won’t solve that problem, a problem which grows bigger and bigger by the The two had a simple idea What if we skipped the BI tooling and infrastructure investments and just gave SaaS companies the answers they needed to grow their revenue? How we do it data science and infrastructure, in a box All your revenue data in one place Answers to critical revenue questions Insights to optimize the full funnel ML models made for SaaS Up and running in days Careers Work with us Can we help you grow? Log In ‹ Comanche Biopharma — WordPress https: comanchebiopharma.com Username or Email Address Password Remember Me Lost your password? ← Go to Comanche Biopharma   Comanche Biopharma Home Contact Us Investor Login Press enter to begin your search Treating the root cause of preeclampsia and sustaining natural Read More Comanche is a preclinical biopharmaceutical company developing novel siRNA compounds for the treatment of Our purpose is to lower the risks of pregnancy and prematurity worldwide by safely sustaining natural pregnancy and allowing for fetal We envision a world where all pregnant women have access to safe and effective therapies that are , and Our mission is to prevent or treat preeclampsia at its root What is Preeclampsia? The burden of preeclampsia is substantial and growing in frequency and It results in patients worldwide with more than ,000 infant and nearly ,000 maternal deaths every Preeclampsia is a leading cause of maternal and neonatal morbidity and mortality with significant costs to healthcare systems and societal It disproportionately affects women who are the youngest, the oldest, black, and the Characterized by hypertension and proteinuria developing after gestational week , there exists no definitive treatment other than delivery of the baby and removal of the Serious adverse outcomes for the mother include seizures, stroke, renal failure and For the baby, either iatrogenic termination or, if delivered prematurely, serious events like intraventricular hemorrhage, periventricular leukomalacia, retinopathy and bronchopulmonary These outcomes are more severe in low and middle income areas of the world where healthcare resources can be scarce and access to care Current standard of care is and involves hospitalization, bedrest and symptomatic treatment (“expectant management”). The objective is to prolong pregnancy and allow the fetus to mature sufficiently to survive ex utero the trade off is continued risk to the mother for the complications of the Our Science Our founding scientists have created hsiRNA compounds capable of specifically and durably silencing the gene in the placenta thereby halting production of the protein responsible for Our approach to this deadly disease unifies three remarkable achievements: recognized as an unambiguous cause of preeclampsia This protein, produced by the placenta and measurable in the plasma of pregnant women, is both diagnostic and prognostic for preeclampsia and is causally responsible for its disease manifestations when Gene silencing via RNA (siRNA) molecules Small snippets of RNA, which typically serve as the blueprint for manufacturing the body’s proteins, can also be used ubiquitously by cells to silence or modulate the expression of target This biological phenomenon, for which the Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine was awarded in , has revolutionized scientific inquiry into gene and protein function and spawned an entirely new class of pharmacologic Three decades of oligonucleotide chemistry Chemically stabilized RNA compounds that function as potent, durable and safe pharmaceutical agents have now been approved by regulatory agencies around the world for indications ranging from orphan disease to population Our chemists have improved upon this successful track record and conjugated siRNA compounds that accumulate in the placenta where they selectively multiple mRNA isoforms coding for while leaving important angiogenic factors Contact Us Notice: JavaScript is required for this Comanche All Rights Copyright © | Website built with ♥ by Skylab . In extra innings, no player earns individual points and there are no additional win points to be earned per inning – only those that have rolled For example, if all seven innings were tied and the game took nine innings to decide a winner, only points, plus win points, would be How We Draft After the last game of every week, the top four point scorers will be named team Each captain will be Scoring to MLB Baseball: Team Parity and Individual Performance Traditional scoring systems run on a strict win loss The Athletes Unlimited scoring system allocates points to the winner of each inning as well as to the winner of the game It also allocates points to individual players based on offensive plays and their degree of impact on the This means even the losing team has a chance to earn points, and a player on a losing team is still Our data team applied our scoring system to Major League Baseball data from the season and found that the Athletes Unlimited scoring system has greater team parity in the league and aligns with conventional measures of individual Read more about the study and simulations Whitepaper: Parity in Athletes Unlimited Softball Traditional scoring systems in similarly scored sports simply count the number of wins and attempt to address team disparity by offering the worst performing team the highest draft pick, or some variation of The Athletes Unlimited system essentially does away with fixed teams by redrafting every roster every week, producing greater team parity and highlighting individual Our data team ran simulations to ensure these goals were Arrow DFMs Home Litepaper Research Recruitment Welcome Technology People Timeline Arrow DFMs Arrow decentralized financial markets (DFMs) are the financial engines of the future Arrow DFMs implement a protocol for creating and settling options on publicly available asset operates through a network of decentralized aggregate counterparties (DACs) financed by liquidity providers in exchange for platform Learn more Follow us on Twitter and get involved on Discord and Telegram Features : A single numeraire is used to settle all contingent This means underliers can be or Decentralized: Code is Law replaces centralized Implemented through a network of Fast and Secure: Runs on Avalanche virtual Front runner resistant and blazing Prolific: Customize and combine options, call spreads, put spreads, futures and The Technology Suite The Arrow protocol implements a decentralized aggregate counterparty (DAC) to act as both a settlement authority and a funding vehicle for each reference We call the DAC coupled with a contract factory a decentralized financial market (DFM). DFMs live on blockchains and generate economies of scale for contingent contract creation and Litepaper Research Research drives our design Click here to see a key set of papers that have helped to shape our The Arrow Team The Arrow Research Group was founded in by Patrick Kiefer and Edward Mehrez . Both are financial economists by At Cornell s Initiative for CryptoCurrencies and Contracts (IC3) workshop in July , Patrick and Edward were joined by Austin Liu and Preston Rozwood to produce a nascent version of the Arrow Arrow is now a global project with partners and team members from New York, Silicon Valley, Singapore, Hong Kong, Dubai and Our backers include Framework Ventures, Alameda Ventures, QCP Soteria, DeFi Capital, RenGen, CMS Holdings, Avalanche Foundation and Delphi Digital Arrow is built on Avalanche Avalanche is an blockchain that is optimized for financial transactions and runs the Ethereum Virtual Machine (EVM). At Gauge, we believe consumers deserve a better way to sell their vehicles, so we’ve created a process that allows you to maximize the sale price of your vehicle without sacrificing Based in Salt Lake City, Utah, Gauge was created by a group of experienced automotive fanatics who saw a need for consumers to be able to get top dollar for their vehicles without the frustration of gathering offers from dealerships or the headache of showing to and negotiating with private How is Gauge different from other car companies? Gauge is not a dealership, and we’re not looking to help you sell your When you accept an offer from us, we’ll buy the vehicle directly from you, and we’ll pay you on the Unlike dealerships, our team is not paid on commission, and unlike consignment groups, we’ll never charge you any Because we don’t retail your vehicle for a profit, we’re not incentivized to buy it for as little as Our goal is aligned with yours: to get you as much as possible for your We only make money if we’re your highest offer and you choose to sell to To read more about how we do this, click here . impact thesis, investor contribution narrative, and underlying assumptions Evidence The extent to which the thesis and underlying assumptions are supported with evidence Alignment The alignment of the impact objectives and metrics with widely accepted goals and standards (e.g., SDGs, IRIS+) Based on this approach, we provide a detailed report of our findings and recommendations for internal use and a summary report that can be shared The BlueMark We recommend improvements for a clear, impact thesis aligned with industry standards, thereby helping clients more accurately and confidently communicate their impact mandate and strategy to the The Types of Clients We Serve We serve a variety of impact investors, including asset managers, asset allocators, and Among asset managers, demand for this service tends to come from fund managers (i.e., those with less than a track record), established fund managers launching their first impact funds, and directly from limited partners in those The Best Timing for Client Verification An impact mandate verification tends to be most relevant early in an impact investor’s journey, either during the fund formation stage or around the time of the fund In some cases, we also conduct verifications for the of existing impact funds to ensure that impact considerations are still central to the The Industry Standards We Use for Verification We draw on a variety of impact investing industry standards, depending on the particular type of client and their particular thesis, investment strategy, and asset These standards include but are not limited to: Impact Management Project (IMP) The GIIN’s IRIS+ impact measurement framework Operating Principles for Impact Management (OPIM) Sustainability Accounting Standards Board (SASB) Sustainable
